      • setPattern

        public MenuPattern setPattern(String... pattern)
        Sets the pattern used to apply this MenuPattern's Buttons to a Menu.

        The Buttons of the pattern must be set using setButton(char, Button) first before calling this method as this method verifies the validity of all characters within the provided String.

        Each string passed to this method will be concatenated together as one pattern string. Newline characters (\r, \n) are ignored. Spaces will do nothing to the slot at the character's position. Underscore characters (_) will forcibly remove the button in the slot at the character's position. All other characters are valid only if registered through the setButton method.

        Parameters:
        pattern - the pattern to set
        Returns:
        this MenuPattern, for chaining

      • apply

        public void apply(Menu menu)
        Applies this MenuPattern to the given Menu.

        Functionally equivalent to calling apply(Menu, boolean) with ignoreEmpty set as true.

        Parameters:
        menu - the Menu to apply to

      • apply

        public void apply(Menu menu,
                  boolean ignoreEmpty)
        Deprecated. Underscores can now be used to represent slots that should forcibly be emptied. apply(Menu) can be used after giving the pattern underscores instead.
        Applies this MenuPattern to the given Menu.

        The ignoreEmpty parameter determines the behavior when encountering a space character in the pattern. If ignoreEmpty is true, the slot occupied by the space character will be left alone; it is otherwise cleared of its current button.

        Parameters:
        menu - the Menu to apply to
        ignoreEmpty - if slots occupied by spaces in the pattern should be left alone
